  {
   "blockIf": "{militaryService} = 'true' or  {workedInDC} = 'false'",
   "category": "Filing Eligibility",
   "elements": [
    {
     "type": "panel",
     "name": "UCX Claim Message",
     "elements": [
      {
       "type": "html",
       "html": {
        "default": "<center><h5>YOUR CLAIM CANNOT BE FILED OVER THE INTERNET</h5></center>\n\n<b>You cannot file an initial claim for Regular Unemployment Compensation over the internet: </b>",
        "es": "<center><h5>Su reclamo no se puede presentar por internet</h5></center>\n\n<b>Usted no puede presentar un reclamo inicial para beneficios de desempleo por internet si:</b>"
       },
       "name": "question2"
      },
      {
       "type": "html",
       "html": {
        "default": "<ul>\n                 <li>You were recently in the military </li>\n </ul>",
        "es": "<ul>\n                 <li>Usted estuvo recientemente en el ej&eacute;rcito</li>\n </ul>"
       },
       "name": "question1",
       "visible": false,
       "visibleIf": "{militaryService} = 'true' "
      },
      {
       "type": "html",
       "html": {
        "default": "<ul>\n                 <li>You worked outside the District of Columbia </li>\n</ul>",
        "es": "<ul>\n                 <li>Usted trabaj&oacute; fuera del Distrito de Columbia</li>\n</ul>"
       },
       "name": "question8",
       "visible": false,
       "visibleIf": "({workedForFederal}= 'false' and  {workedInDC} = 'false')"
      },
      {
       "type": "html",
       "html": {
        "default": "\n<b>If you are a District of Columbia resident,</b> you need to file your initial claim in person at one of our One Stop Centers. Claims are taken by appointment. To make an appointment, please call 724-7000. One Stop Centers which take initial claims are located at: \n          <ul>         \n                  <li>5171 South Dakota Avenue, N.E., 2nd Floor </li>\n                  <li>3720 Martin Luther King, Jr.Avenue, S.E. </li>\n          </ul>\n\n<b>If you are a Maryland resident,</b> you may file your unemployment claim against the District of Columbia through the Maryland Unemployment Office by phone. The number is 301-313-8000.\n</br></br>\n<b>If you live in any other state,</b> you should report to the nearest unemployment office in your state of residence to file a claim against the District of Columbia.\n",
        "es": "\n<b>Si usted es habitante del Distrito de Columbia,</b> necesita presentar su reclamo inicial en persona en uno de nuestros Centros de Trabajo (American Job Centers). Los reclamos son tomados por medio de citas. Para hacer una cita, por favor llame al 202-724-7000. Los Centros de Trabajo (American Job Centers) que toman reclamos iniciales est&aacute;n ubicados en:\n          <ul>         \n                  <li>5171 South Dakota Avenue, N.E., 2do Piso</li>\n                  <li>3720 Martin Luther King, Jr.Avenue, S.E.</li>\n          </ul>\n\n<b>Si usted es habitante de Maryland,</b> necesita presentar su reclamo inicial en el Distrito de Columbia a trav&eacute;s dela oficina de desempleo del estado de Maryland. Puede llamar al 301-313-8000 para m&aacute;s informaci&oacute;n.\n</br></br>\n<b>Si usted vive en otro estado,</b> debe reportarse a la oficina de desempleo m&aacute;s cercana para presentar un reclamo dirigido al Distrito de Columbia.\n"
       },
       "name": "question7"
      }
     ],
     "visible": false,
     "visibleIf": "{militaryService} = 'true' or  ({workedForFederal}= 'false' and  {workedInDC} = 'false')"
    }
   ],
   "name": "Military and Out of State Claim",
   "title": {
    "default": "Military and Out of State Claim",
    "es": "Reclamo militar y fuera del estado"
   },
   "visible": false,
