  {
   "category": "Benefit Rights and Responsibilities",
   "elements": [
    {
     "type": "html",
     "html": {
      "default": "<b>Your Benefit Rights and Responsibilities:   </b>\n<br><br>\nYou have now completed your application for Unemployment Compensation benefits with the District of Columbia. Before submitting your claim, please review the information below summarizing your Rights and Responsibilities as an Unemployment Compensation claimant. We suggest you make a copy of this page for reference. \n<br><br>\nYou must read the Claimant’s Rights and Responsibilities handbook located at the following links: Claimant's Rights and Responsibilities Handbook (<a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Rights%20and%20Responsibilities.pdf\">English</a>,  <a  class=\"text-danger\"href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Spanish%20Revised.pdf \">Spanish</a>, <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Vietnamese.pdf\">Vietnamese</a>, <a  class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Korean.pdf\">Korean</a>,<a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/French.pdf\"> French</a>,<a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Chinese.pdf \"> Chinese</a>, <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Amharic.pdf \">Amharic</a>) \n<br><br>\nYou must comply with all requirements contained in this handbook; failure to comply may result in denial of benefits. \n<br><br>\nYou must provide details about your separation from your last 30 day employer if you are contacted by a Claims Examiner. \n<br><br>\nYou must certify for benefits weekly by completing a continued claim form. You may submit your continued claim form over the Internet, by telephone or by mail. Instructions for completing your continued claim form are located at the following link: <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Help/INSTRUCTIONS_FOR_COMPLETING_THE_CONTINUED_CLAIM_FORM.pdf \"> INSTRUCTIONS FOR COMPLETING THE CONTINUED CLAIM FORM </a> \n<br><br>\nYou must be able and available for work and actively seeking work. For every week you claim benefits, you must make at least two job contacts. \n<br><br>\nIf you work during a week that you claim benefits, you must report all wages earned for that week on your continued claim form. You must report your gross earnings before any deductions are made by your employer for taxes, health benefits, etc. You must report your gross earnings for the week during which you worked, even if you are not paid that week. <br><br>\nIf you receive severance pay for a week that you claim benefits, you must report this on your continued claim form and indicate the gross amount of your severance pay for the week. \n<br><br>\nThe District of Columbia has a one week waiting period. No benefits are paid for this waiting week. \n<br><br>\nIf you owe child support, a deduction of at least 25% of your weekly benefit amount may be made and applied to satisfy your child support obligation. \n<br><br>\nYou have the option of having your benefit payments deposited directly into your savings or checking account via direct deposit.\n<br><br>\nIf you choose not to use direct deposit, then you will receive your benefit payments via a debit card that is issued to all claimants. \n<br><br>\nYou are liable to repay any benefits that are overpaid to you. \n \n ",
      "es": "<b>Derechos y responsabilidades de su beneficio por desempleo: </b>\n<br>\n<br>\nUsted ha completado su solicitud de reclamo para beneficios por desempleo en el Distrito de Columbia. Antes de someter su reclamo, revise la informaci&oacute;n a continuaci&oacute;n que resume sus responsabilidades como reclamante de beneficios por desempleo. Se le recomienda que imprima esta p&aacute;gina para su referencia en el futuro. \n<br>\n<br>\nDebe leer el folleto de los Derechos y Responsabilidades del Reclamante que ser&aacute; enviado por correo y est&aacute; disponible en el siguiente enlace: \n<br>\n<br>\nDerechos y Responsabilidades del Reclamante (<a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Rights%20and%20Responsibilities.pdf\">ingl&eacute;s</a>, <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Spanish%20Revised.pdf\">espa&ntilde;ol</a>, <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Vietnamese.pdf\">Vietnamese</a>, <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Korean.pdf\">Korean</a>, <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/French.pdf\">French</a>, <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Chinese.pdf \">Chinese</a>, <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Amharic.pdf \">Amharic</a>) \n<br>\n<br>\nUsted debe cumplir con todos los requisitos en este folleto. Falta de cumplir con los requisitos puede resultar en su descalificaci&oacute;n para beneficios de desempleo. \n<br>\n<br>\nUsted debe proporcionar en detalle la raz&oacute;n por la cual usted dej&oacute; el empleo que tuvo durante los &uacute;ltimos treinta (30) d&iacute;as si es contactado por un Examinador de Reclamos. \nUsted debe completar el formulario de reclamo semanal. Puede presentarlo por correo, internet o tel&eacute;fono. Instrucciones para completar el formulario de reclamo semanal est&aacute; disponible en el siguiente enlace: \n<br>\n<br>\n <a class=\"text-danger\" href=\"https://does.dcnetworks.org/initialclaims/Help/INSTRUCTIONS_FOR_COMPLETING_THE_CONTINUED_CLAIM_FORM.pdf \">Instrucciones para completar el formulario de reclamo semanal. </a> \nUsted debe estar disponible para trabajar y debe estar buscando trabajo cada semana. Usted debe proporcionar dos (2) b&uacute;squedas de trabajo por semana. \nSi usted trabaj&oacute; durante cualquier semana reclamada, usted debe de reportar sus ingresos brutos (antes de las deducciones de impuestos federales, estatales, beneficios de salud, etc.) por esa semana en su formulario de reclamo semanal. Usted debe reportar sus ingresos brutos por esa semana independientemente de que no se la haya pagado en esa semana. \n<br>\n<br>\nSi usted recibe indemnizaci&oacute;n por despido en cualquier semana que recibe beneficios por desempleo, usted debe reportar la cantidad exacta de la indemnizaci&oacute;n por despido en su reclamo semanal. \nUsted debe entender que hay una semana de espera en el Distrito de Columbia en que no se la paga ning&uacute;n beneficio por desempleo por esa semana. \n<br>\n<br>\nSi usted paga manutenci&oacute;n de menores, puede ser que se le retenga un veinticinco (25) por ciento de su beneficio semanal para satisfacer su obligaci&oacute;n de manutenci&oacute;n de menores. \nUsted tiene la opci&oacute;n de depositar sus beneficios de desempleo directamente a su cuenta bancaria de ahorros o de cheques.\n<br>\n<br>\nSi desea inscribirse al dep&oacute;sito directo, usted debe completar la solicitud de dep&oacute;sito directo que se le enviar&aacute; por correo. \n<br>\n<br>\nUsted es responsable de pagar cualquier beneficio de desempleo que se le sobre pague."
     },
     "name": "question9",
     "tag": "Optimum Html"
    }
